Subject: [PATCH 5/8] add CTA hook to plain-english section
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes the plain-english explainer with two actions:
- Primary: "Commission an Audit →" (bold safety-orange button anchored
  to #pricing) so readers who grok the pitch have a clear next step
- Secondary: "See a Sample Report" ghost link that opens the
  /report-mockup.html in a new tab — shows the deliverable to anyone
  who wants evidence-of-craft before committing

Plus a trust strip beneath: pulse-dot + "72-Hour Turnaround · No
Retainer · Full Refund If We Miss The Bar" in mono caps. Removes the
remaining objections (time, lock-in, risk) in one line.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
